dataframe.Year = dataframe.Year.astype(str)
dataframe.Month = dataframe.Month.astype(str)
dataframe.DayofMonth = dataframe.DayofMonth.astype(str)

date = dataframe.DayofMonth + '-' + dataframe.Month + '-' + dataframe.Year
dataframe.insert(0,'date',date)
dataframe.date = pd.to_datetime(date)
dataframe.drop(['Year', 'Month', 'DayofMonth'], axis=1, inplace=True)

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 6.85M flight in the dataset with 10 columns (date, DayOfWeek, UniqueCarrier, FlightNum, ActualElapsedTime, CRSElapsedTime, AirTime, ArrDelay, DepDelay, Distance). There are 7 columns numeric and 3 columns categorical.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The most feature interest at dataset (ActualElapsedTime, CRSElapsedTime) to predict delay.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

The strongest columns effect on each flight is (DayOfWeek, Distance, AirTime, UniqueCarrier,) this column will support me to predict the flight delay.

Bin = np.arange(100000, 1100000 + 100000,100000)
order =dataframe.DayOfWeek.value_counts().index

sb.countplot(data=dataframe, x='DayOfWeek',color= sb.color_palette()[0],order=order);
plt.title('Number of flights for each day')
plt.xlabel('Day of week')
plt.ylabel('Number of flight')
plt.xticks(rotation=20)
plt.yticks(Bin,Bin);

Approximately all days have the same number of flights except (Sunday, Saturday)
